OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782307135
OL,3,CSuncream, frozen toys and shade: How
OL,4,Cto keep pets safe in the heat
OL,6,FPlace fans around the house to keep
OL,7,Fthe air circulating, remembering not
OL,8,Fto point the fan directly at your pet.
OL,10,FCat Protection recommends that during
OL,11,Fthe warmest parts of the day, try to
OL,12,Fkeep your cat inside between 10am and
OL,13,F3pm.
OL,15,FYou should also make sure clean and
OL,16,Fcold water is available. Ice cubes can
OL,17,Fbe put into the water bowl.
OL,19,FFor cats, you can spread water bowls
OL,20,Faround the house so they have easy
OL,21,Faccess.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
