OL,3,CSuncream, frozen toys and shade: How
OL,4,Cto keep pets safe in the heat
OL,6,FWalking during cooler times of the day
OL,8,FTake your dog out for a walk earlier
OL,9,Fin the morning or later in the evening
OL,10,Fwhen it's cooler.
OL,12,FDon't run or cycle with your dog in
OL,13,Fthe heat.
OL,15,FThe RSCPA also recommends checking how
OL,16,Fhot the pavement is before walking. If
OL,17,Fit's too hot to touch with your hand
OL,18,Ffor five seconds, then it's too hot
OL,19,Ffor your dog's paws.
OL,21,FUse pet-safe suncream
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
