OL,3,CSuncream, frozen toys and shade: How
OL,4,Cto keep pets safe in the heat
OL,6,FThis can stop them from feeling
OL,7,Foverheated during hotter spells. Make
OL,8,Fsure that your cat can get away from
OL,9,Fthe bottle if they choose.
OL,11,FRegular grooming to reduce the density
OL,12,Fof their coat
OL,14,FRegularly brushing your dog can help
OL,15,Fremove excess hair and knots, so they
OL,16,Fhave a "less dense coat".
OL,18,FHow to spot sunburn in your pet
OL,20,FThere are symptoms to look out for in
OL,21,Fcase your pet gets sunburnt:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
