OL,3,CSuncream, frozen toys and shade: How
OL,4,Cto keep pets safe in the heat
OL,6,FIf you think your pet has sunburn, you
OL,7,Fshould bring them indoors immediately
OL,8,Fand contact your vet for advice.
OL,10,FSigns of heatstroke
OL,12,FYou should contact your vet
OL,13,Fimmediately if you think your pet
OL,14,Fmight have heatstroke, the RSPCA says.
OL,16,FThe symptoms to look out for include:
